// =============================================================================
// core.theory_interop.bridges — canonical cross-framework translations
// =============================================================================
//
// Each sub-module ships a *canonical bridge* between two registered
// framework-axiom packages: a directed set of trusted-boundary
// translation markers documenting the categorical / structural image
// of every operator from the source framework in the target framework.
//
// Bridges enable downstream `core.theory_interop.translate(source,
// target, partial_map)` invocations (VVA §10.2 / §21.7) to compose
// chains of @framework_translate axioms without re-deriving the
// pointwise mapping from scratch.
//
// V1 catalogue (this commit):
//   owl2_to_htt        — owl2_fs → lurie_htt (24 markers, VVA C7b)
//   oc_dc_bridge       — Articulation ↔ Enactment round-trip (Theorem 16.10)
//
// V2 additions (tracked in VVA §16.6 F6):
//   owl2_to_baez_dolan      — n-categorical embedding
//   owl2_to_schreiber_dcct  — cohesive ∞-topos embedding
//   owl2_to_connes          — operator-algebraic embedding
//   owl2_to_petz            — quantum-state embedding
// =============================================================================

public mount core.theory_interop.bridges.owl2_to_htt;
public mount core.theory_interop.bridges.oc_dc_bridge;
